==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Row
<hw>Row</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Abbrev. fr. <ets>rouse</ets>,
n.]</ety> <def>A noisy, turbulent quarrel or disturbance; a brawl.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Row</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Row
<hw>Row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>rowe</ets>,
<ets>rawe</ets>, <ets>rewe</ets>, AS. <ets>r⟦amac⟧w</ets>,
<ets>r<?/w</ets>; probably akin to D. <ets>rij</ets>, G.
<ets>reihe</ets>; cf. Skr. <ets>r<?/kh⟦amac⟧</ets> a line,
stroke.]</ety> <def>A series of persons or things arranged in a
continued line; a line; a rank; a file; <as>as, a <ex>row</ex> of trees;
a <ex>row</ex> of houses or columns</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And there were windows in three <qex>rows</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1
Kings vii. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The bright seraphim in burning <qex>row</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Row culture</b></col> <fld>(Agric.)</fld>, <cd>the
practice of cultivating crops in drills.</cd> -- <col><b>Row of
points</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>the points on a line, infinite
in number, as the points in which a pencil of rays is intersected by a
line.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Row</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Row
<hw>Row</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Rowed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Rowing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>r<?/wan</ets>; akin to
D. <ets>roeijen</ets>, MHG. <ets>r⟦uum⟧ejen</ets>, Dan. <ets>roe</ets>,
Sw. <ets>ro</ets>, Icel. <ets>r<?/a</ets>, L. <ets>remus</ets> oar, Gr.
<?/, Skr. <ets>aritra</ets>. ⟦root⟧8. Cf. <er>Rudder</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To propel with oars, as a boat or vessel, along the
surface of water; <as>as, to <ex>row</ex> a boat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To transport in a boat propelled with oars; <as>as,
to <ex>row</ex> the captain ashore in his barge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Row</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Row
<hw>Row</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To use the oar; <as>as,
to <ex>row</ex> well</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be moved by oars; <as>as, the boat <ex>rows</ex>
easily</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Row</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 6 ====
HEADWORD: Row
<hw>Row</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of rowing; excursion in a
rowboat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rowable</ent>⟦br⟧
